com.group16.proj

Class Entry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.group16.proj.Entry

  • public class Entry
extends java.lang.Object
    Formats and stores the data from the boarder wait times of ONE BOARDER CROSSING per Entry Object.
    Performs basic operations on the data for better use in the Controller class
    Author:
    alexgotsko

      • tempTime

        private int[][] tempTime
        2d Integer array used to temporarily store wait times for each hour interval in a given day. [i][] - hour of day (0 to 23), [][i] - wait time for vehicle type (0 gives commercial, 1 gives normal).

        private java.util.ArrayList<int[][]> wTime

    • Constructor Detail

      • Entry

        public Entry()
        Default Entry Constructor Sets up the data structure

        Initiate new array list of entry dates and set the first entry to "01-01"
        Initiate new array list of wait times.
        Create new 2d array for storing wait times for each hour interval.
        Add 2d array to the array list of wait times.

        One entry object per border crossing location.

    • Method Detail

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry(java.lang.String d,
                     int h,
                     int t)
        Takes a date as a string a recorded time as an integer and the logged wait time for that time as an integer. Checks to see if the last index of the entry objects day is the same if it is not then it adds a new day to the eDate arraylist, adds the complete temp array of wait times to the wTime list and adds empty arrays for the wait times. It then adds the hour and the wait time to the temporary wait time array.
        Parameters:
        d - String representation of the Date
        h - Integer representation of the recorded hour
        t - Integer representation of the logged wait time

        Returns:
